# Cloudflare Pages / Workers static-asset headers.
# The strict Content-Security-Policy is the P0 half of the host-integrity
# hardening in DESIGN.md section 10.2: no inline script, no eval, no third-party
# origins, so any backdoor must live in the one first-party bundle the
# reproducible build and release-hash log (10.1) can watch. connect-src widens
# to the real relay and push origins when they exist (P4/P6).
#
# NOTE: the "/*" line below is a Cloudflare _headers URL PATH GLOB (it matches
# every route), NOT a C-style /* */ comment. Comments in this file are
# '#'-prefixed; the indented lines under "/*" are the headers applied to all
# responses. See developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'none'; manifest-src 'self'
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  Integrity-Policy: blocked-destinations=(script)
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), camera=(), microphone=(), payment=()
